other_tests.findings: Mildly hypocellular bone marrow with maturing trilineage hematopoiesis; no abnormal cells found on immunoperoxidase staining.
Slightly hypocellular marrow with a mildly increased number of CD117+ mast cells, including spindle-shaped cells.
Pathological examination revealed necrosis, fibrosis, and bone remodeling, with prominent osteoclastic activity.
